<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880428-0143 </DOCNO><HL> US Sprint Is Awarded Contract </HL><SO> </SO><CO> UT GTE TEX </CO><IN> TEL </IN><DATELINE> KANSAS CITY, Mo.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   US Sprint said a Texas Air Corp. subsidiary granted it a contract valued at more than $100 million for long-distance telecommunications services.    System One, Texas Air's information and telecommunications subsidiary, said it chose US Sprint, a joint venture of United Telecommunications Inc. and GTE Corp., because its extensive use of fiber optics offers high-quality transmission.    System One added that it wanted to have two principal providers of long-distance services; American Telephone andamp; Telegraph Co. is the other. </TEXT></DOC>